PLANS by <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Historic_Scotland" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Historic_Scotland" target="_blank">Historic Scotland</a> to charge visitors entry to <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow_Cathedral" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow_Cathedral" target="_blank">Glasgow Cathedral</a> have been put on hold as hundreds of <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/People" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/People" target="_blank">people</a> voice &shyoppositionOfficials of the Kirk Session of <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow_Cathedral" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow_Cathedral" target="_blank">Glasgow Cathedral</a> said they had no formal notification from the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quango" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quango" target="_blank">government body</a> but remained opposed to charging which might particularly hit <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patient" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patient" target="_blank">patients</a> and staff at the neighbouring <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Glasgow" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Glasgow" target="_blank">Glasgow</a> Royal InfirmaryThe <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cathedral" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cathedral" target="_blank">cathedral</a> was gifted to the people of Scotland and is managed by the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_agency" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Government_agency" target="_blank">government agency</a> in a way similar to <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dunfermline_Abbey" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dunfermline_Abbey" target="_blank">Dunfermline Abbey</a> and <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edinburgh" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edinburgh" target="_blank">Edinburgh</a> and <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stirling_Castle" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stirling_Castle" target="_blank">Stirling</a> ca